The expected value of \(Y_1\) is \(E(Y_1) = \frac{1}{2\theta} = \frac{1}{4} = 0.25\).  
The expected value of \(Y_2\) is \(E(Y_2) = \frac{3}{2\theta} = \frac{3}{4} = 0.75\).  
