The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. Let \(N\) be the number of observations less than 27.3. Then \(N\) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\).

Thus,  
\[P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(N \geq 7) = P(N = 7) + P(N = 8).\]

Calculate each probability:  
- \(P(N = 7) = \binom{8}{7} \cdot (0.7)^7 \cdot (0.3)^1 = 8 \cdot (0.7)^7 \cdot 0.3\)  
- \(P(N = 8) = \binom{8}{8} \cdot (0.7)^8 \cdot (0.3)^0 = 1 \cdot (0.7)^8 \cdot 1 = (0.7)^8\)

