D & =\{x: x \text { is a diamond, a heart, or a spade }\} .
\end{aligned}
$$
Find $P(A)$ The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The probability \(P(A)\) is the probability of drawing a jack, queen, or king from a standard deck of 52 cards. There are 4 jacks, 4 queens, and 4 kings, for a total of 12 favorable outcomes. Since each card has a probability of \( \frac{1}{52} \), \( P(A) = \frac{12}{52} \).

